{"TopicId":155014,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.4.x] BDArmory Continued v1.2.2.2 [8/8/2018] \u002B Vessel Mover, Camera Tools, BDMk22, Destruction Effects, Burn Together","CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-14T23:16:30Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"qromodynmc","CreatedById":87139,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T21:49:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485031837\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174072\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LtTucker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, LtTucker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having the same problem as you, as soon as I go above 200m it breaks. I found a work around as I\u00A0was making another bomber, if you right click on any of the bombs and set them to in cargo bay their trajectory is fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope this helps you out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I\u0027ll try that. It seems like a bug to me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T17:48:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe would like to give a shout out to our latest member, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/137239-thedog/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022137239\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/137239-thedog/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TheDog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the team \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qromodynmc","CreatedById":87139,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T19:34:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485031837\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174072\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LtTucker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, LtTucker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having the same problem as you, as soon as I go above 200m it breaks. I found a work around as I\u00A0was making another bomber, if you right click on any of the bombs and set them to in cargo bay their trajectory is fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope this helps you out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly i couldnt make it work, it\u0027s so annoying \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gomker","CreatedById":141269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T01:18:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222930832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485113677\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002287139\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022qromodynmc\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/22/2017 at 1:34 PM, qromodynmc said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly i couldnt make it work, it\u0027s so annoying \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a template craft in a folder called /Crafts \u00A0under the BDArmory directory named \u0022 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/blob/master/BahaTurret/Distribution/GameData/BDArmory/craft/BDA%20-%20TestPlaneAI%20-%20v3.craft\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(64,120,192);text-decoration:none;font-family:\u0027-apple-system\u0027, BlinkMacSystemFont, \u0027Segoe UI\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \u0027Apple Color Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Symbol\u0027;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;word-spacing:0px;\u0022 title=\u0022BDA - TestPlaneAI - v3.craft\u0022\u003EBDA - TestPlaneAI - v3.craft\u003C/a\u003E \u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you load that up and see if the problem still exists. The issue you are describing was worked on in the previous release under this \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/77\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eissue\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n//Edit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually this has this fix was *not* released just yet, I just checked the change log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-24T01:22:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2017 01:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by gomker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qromodynmc","CreatedById":87139,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T12:33:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222932319\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485220736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022141269\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gomker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, gomker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a template craft in a folder called /Crafts \u00A0under the BDArmory directory named \u0022 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/blob/master/BahaTurret/Distribution/GameData/BDArmory/craft/BDA%20-%20TestPlaneAI%20-%20v3.craft\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(64,120,192);text-decoration:none;font-family:\u0027-apple-system\u0027, BlinkMacSystemFont, \u0027Segoe UI\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \u0027Apple Color Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Emoji\u0027, \u0027Segoe UI Symbol\u0027;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;word-spacing:0px;\u0022 title=\u0022BDA - TestPlaneAI - v3.craft\u0022\u003EBDA - TestPlaneAI - v3.craft\u003C/a\u003E \u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you load that up and see if the problem still exists. The issue you are describing was worked on in the previous release under this \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/77\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eissue\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n//Edit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually this has this fix was *not* released just yet, I just checked the change log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, problem exist. Hope someone fixes it soon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atatra","CreatedById":122338,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T15:39:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was wondering if somebody could help me with a bug i have? acknowledging the fact that i\u0027m running the 1.2.0 version of BDAc on 1.2.2.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery time i fire a gun the bullet tracers/trails are purple, missing texture shade to be exact, and the screen for the tracking ball and FLIR pod are flat purple, can\u0027t use them at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a fix for this or is an unavoidable part of using BDAc 1.2 on ksp 1.2.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T15:47:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222932842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485272381\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atatra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Atatra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a fix for this or is an unavoidable part of using BDAc 1.2 on ksp 1.2.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi as you presume using the wrong version of the mod with your game will cause issues that there is no fix for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue you are experiencing is caused by BDA not being able to load the shaders for tracers etc and the only fix was a rebuild of the shaders and a code update in order to load them,\u003Cu\u003E There is no possible fix for you aside from to use the correct version for your game\u00A0 \u003C/u\u003E\u003Cs\u003E \u003C/s\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there is a fix but would involve rebuilding the shaders and then writing the code to load them and then recompiling the mod yourself , but that wouldn\u0027t fix the two dozen other problems that that particular release of BDAc has.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-24T15:48:33Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2017 03:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by SpannerMonkey(smce)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atatra","CreatedById":122338,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T15:48:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso i\u0027m assuming i\u0027ll have to wait until there\u0027s an official release of BDAc for ksp 1.2.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T16:06:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222932850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485272926\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atatra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Atatra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso i\u0027m assuming i\u0027ll have to wait until there\u0027s an official release of BDAc for ksp 1.2.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDAc release v0.11.1.6\u00A0adresses your\u00A0issue\u00A0... it is easily found by going to Papa Joes Soup on Github and looking\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll give you a hint, it can be found below:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-24T16:08:31Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2017 04:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DoctorDavinci\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atatra","CreatedById":122338,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T16:08:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222932855\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485273967\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDAc release v0.1.16\u00A0adresses your\u00A0issue\u00A0...\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh awesome, thanks for the help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkOwl57","CreatedById":161624,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T16:17:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485031837\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174072\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LtTucker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/21/2017 at 2:50 PM, LtTucker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif you right click on any of the bombs and set them to in cargo bay their trajectory is fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr just fly at ridiculously low altitude with some snake eyes and lay waste to the world below\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stickman939","CreatedById":131481,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T21:20:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222932865\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485274635\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DarkOwl57\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, DarkOwl57 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr just fly at ridiculously low altitude with some snake eyes and lay waste to the world below\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr we could just nuke it! That\u0027s a problem solver!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkOwl57","CreatedById":161624,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-24T21:29:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222933173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485292824\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131481\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022stickman939\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, stickman939 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr we could just nuke it! That\u0027s a problem solver!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n#TheAmericanWay\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nerfclasher","CreatedById":158707,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-26T13:40:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongrats \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/137239-thedog/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022137239\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/137239-thedog/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TheDog\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for joining the team as a former BDAc member it\u0027s definitely a\u00A0honor to be\u00A0selected\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-26T13:41:15Z\u0022 title=\u002201/26/2017 01:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 26, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Nerfclasher\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"drtricky","CreatedById":154647,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-27T02:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just tried utilizing fixed 35mm oerlikons on an aircraft, and all the rounds detonated ~500 m in front of my aircraft, even though the detonation range was set to 3500 m. Can anyone else double check the oerlikons?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheBeardyPenguin","CreatedById":166637,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-28T23:35:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any way to stop guard mode firing at missiles/bombs?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere\u0027s the option to set it to shoot at just missiles or everything.. Could I make it only shoot at vessels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-29T03:10:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222937667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485646518\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166637\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheBeardyPenguin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, TheBeardyPenguin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any way to stop guard mode firing at missiles/bombs?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere\u0027s the option to set it to shoot at just missiles or everything.. Could I make it only shoot at vessels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently there is only the two modes for guard mode targeting ... Missiles or all craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeel free to open a feature request on Github ... We use the built in Github issues tracker to keep record of bugs, enhancements and feature requests as it is difficult to keep track of bug reports and all the great ideas that 